   NAME
	ENDSKIP - Terminates a SKIP search block in a script file.

   FORMAT
	ENDSKIP

   TEMPLATE
	(none)

   PATH
	Internal

   FUNCTION
	ENDSKIP is used in scripts to define the end of a SKIP search 
	block (The SKIP command allows you to jump over intervening 
	commands if a certain condition is met). When an ENDSKIP is 
	encountered, execution of the script resumes at the line following 
	the ENDSKIP. The return code is set to 5 (WARN).

   SEE ALSO
	SKIP
